Content from https://docs.pytest.org/en/stable/how-to/parametrize.html:

# How to parametrize fixtures and test functions

pytest enables test parametrization at several levels:

    @pytest.mark.parametrize("n, expected", [(1, 1), (2, 4), (3, 9)])
    def test_square(n, expected):
        assert n * n == expected

## Parametrizing fixtures

    @pytest.fixture(params=["sqlite", "postgres", "mysql"])
    def db(request):
        return connect(request.param)

    def test_read(db):
        ...

Every test that uses this fixture runs three times — once per backend.

## Indirect parametrization

    @pytest.mark.parametrize("db", ["pg://a", "pg://b"], indirect=True)
    def test_conn(db):
        ...

With indirect=True, the parametrize value goes to the fixture body (as request.param), not the test.
